The '''Beembe''' are a [[Bantu peoples|Bantu]] people living in central southern [[Republic of the Congo|Congo-Brazzaville]], precisely in the upper [[Bounza River|Bouenza]] Basin. It is a [[Bakongo]] clan, to which its neighbours belong as well.

Beembe society is economically based on agriculture.

