The '''Burmese census''' is an official count of the human population in [[Burma]] (Myanmar).
==History== The earliest census on record in Burmese history was taken in 1359 in the [[Pinya Kingdom]]. The first nationwide census was taken in 1638, and it was followed by two other nationwide censuses in 1784 and 1803.<ref>{{cite book | last=Harvey | first=G. E.| title=History of Burma: From the Earliest Times to 10 March 1824 | publisher=Frank Cass & Co. Ltd | year=1925 | location = London | pages=194, 269–270}}</ref> The first modern census was taken in 1891 in the [[British rule in Burma|British colonial period]]. It was carried out in 10-year intervals until 1941.<ref>{{cite web |title=President U Thein Sein attends the meeting to clarify country-wide census-taking (2014) process |url=http://m.president-office.gov.mm/en/?q=briefing-room/news/2013/08/02/id-2497 |accessdate=22 October 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023061325/http://m.president-office.gov.mm/en/?q=briefing-room%2Fnews%2F2013%2F08%2F02%2Fid-2497 |archivedate=23 October 2013 |df=dmy }}</ref> In the post-independence area, the census has been conducted 3 times, in 1973, 1983, and [[2014 Burma Census|2014]].
==2014 Census== {{main article|2014 Burma Census}} The last census was conducted by the [[Ministry of Immigration and Population]]'s Department of Population, and was funded by Western donors, at a cost of {{US$|74 million}}, and supervised by the [[United Nations Population Fund]].<ref>{{cite journal|date=February 2014|title=Ethnicity without Meaning, Data without Context|volume=Transnational Institute|url=http://www.tni.org/sites/www.tni.org/files/download/bpb_13.pdf}}</ref>
