{{Infobox criminal | name = Penelope Kenny | birth_date = Unknown | birth_place = <!--Unknown--> | death_date = {{Death date|1739|12|27}} | death_place = [[New Hampshire]] | conviction = Murder | conviction_penalty = Death by hanging | conviction_status = Executed }}
'''Penelope Kenny''' (died December 27, 1739) was executed by [[hanging]] for the murder of her child in [[New Hampshire]] along with [[Sarah Simpson]], who was also convicted of murdering her child.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=AGA_FEsKRioC&pg=PA76&lpg=PA76&dq=Penelope+Kenny+executed&source=bl&ots=mRK5iQ9QFu&sig=RFVTqFh5ne4GTX4vUdeqR0VG2XI&hl=en&ei=Y9KyTpnVDMaHgwf5kYmSBA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=6&ved=0CEAQ6AEwBQ#v=onepage&q=Penelope%20Kenny%20executed&f=false Women who kill]</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.pl/books?id=3FCACQAAQBAJ&pg=PT38&lpg=PT38&dq=%22Sarah+Simpson%22+-wikipedia+infanticide&source=bl&ots=cY8FH2m0Md&sig=0zUJuhWhJr-QVtB6yxbmpFoptPQ&hl=fr&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwji1Lf-pP7TAhUC6xQKHaQzA8gQ6AEIPDAC#v=onepage&q=%22Sarah%20Simpson%22%20-wikipedia%20infanticide&f=false|title=Historic Crimes & Justice in Portsmouth, New Hampshire|last=Ferland|first=Dr David|date=2014-05-27|publisher=Arcadia Publishing|isbn=9781625847140|language=en}}</ref>
